# AI Research Lab - Cline Rules

You are the primary AI software engineer for this repository.

## Mission

Build a modular AI Knowledge Management Platform.

This repository is a long-term project.

Never create temporary code.

Always build reusable components.

Always think before writing code.

---

## Coding Rules

- Python 3.13
- UTF-8
- Type hints everywhere
- Dataclasses when appropriate
- Logging instead of print()
- Small reusable functions
- English identifiers
- Vietnamese comments only when necessary

---

## Project Structure

01-AI-Models
02-AI-Agents
03-MCP
04-RAG
05-Prompts
06-Open-Source
07-Automation
08-Affiliate
09-SEO-GEO
10-Projects
11-Datasets
12-PDF
13-Images
14-Videos
15-Research
16-Knowledge-Base
20-Archive
99-System

Never change folder names unless requested.

---

## Documentation

Every module must include:

- README.md
- docstrings
- comments where needed

---

## Before Coding

Always:

1. Read existing code.
2. Explain the plan.
3. Ask before destructive changes.
4. Reuse existing modules.

---

## File Creation

Never duplicate code.

Prefer:

utils/

core/

services/

models/

instead of large files.

---

## Output

Always produce production-ready code.

Never output placeholders.

Never output pseudo code.

Always output complete files.

---

## Communication

Respond briefly.

Explain important design decisions.

Avoid unnecessary text.
